-- Bank of America's Holliday Says U.S. Should Boost Energy R&D Investment
-- Theo Mullen
-- 2010-06-15T21:28:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/bank-of-america-s-holliday-says-u-s-should-boost-energy-r-d-investment.html

          
          
             Charles Holliday, chairman of Bank
of America, said the U.S. should boost energy research and
development spending to $16 billion each year and focus that
spending on solar energy, biofuels and nuclear energy.  
 Holliday spoke in a interview on CNBC’s ‘Fast Money’
program.  
          
          


  


        